  "title": "fix(insights): pass correct sendEvent to html template",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nThere was an existing prop called `sendEvent`, which we passed through to the component when we introduced html templates. However, this sendEvent was actually sendEventToInsights, which is of course problematic, as it doesn't match the documentation, nor does it add the necessary conversion from a simple \"three argument\" form to \"object form\".\r\n\r\nThis PR changes the prop that existed from `sendEventToInsights` to `sendEvent` which comes from the connector.\r\n\r\ndiscovered in https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/discussions/5447#discussioncomment-4779169\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\n`sendEvent` in html templates behaves as it should, and uses `sendEvent` from the connector.\r\n\r\nThis PR is fairly urgent, as the documentation has been updated to use `sendEvent` instead of `bindEvent` (which didn't have this bug)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Reviewer notes**\r\n\r\nHide whitespace, as that's the only thing changed in the snapshots because they were indented wrong :)",
